The paper deals with algorithms for computing morphs between convex drawings of a plane graph, which involves concepts from computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the algorithm, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.DM). The paper's focus on preserving convexity and using piecewise linear curves suggests that it may also be relevant to the study of geometric representations of graphs (cs.GR) and possibly even computer graphics (cs.SI).
